<%- include('../partials/header', { seo: seo }) %>

<section class="section legal-page">
  <div class="site-container legal-page-inner">
    <p class="legal-eyebrow">Legal</p>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="legal-updated">Last updated: 19 June 2026</p>

    <p>This Privacy Policy explains how SiteCrew ("we", "us") collects, uses, and protects personal data when you use <a href="<%= seo.canonical.replace('/privacy', '/') %>">sitecrew.uk</a>. We process data in line with UK GDPR and the Data Protection Act 2018.</p>

    <h2>1. Data we collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Account data: name, email, password hash, role (worker or company).</li>
      <li>Profile data: trade interests, location, availability, bio, photos, certificates, company details.</li>
      <li>Activity data: job applications, messages, posts, notifications, and platform interactions.</li>
      <li>Technical data: IP address, browser type, device data, cookies, and security logs.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. How we use data</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Provide and secure the platform.</li>
      <li>Match workers with relevant jobs and companies.</li>
      <li>Enable messaging, applications, and account management.</li>
      <li>Moderate content and prevent abuse or fraud.</li>
      <li>Improve features, support users, and meet legal obligations.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Legal bases</h2>
    <p>We rely on contract performance, legitimate interests (platform safety and improvement), consent where required (for example marketing cookies if enabled), and legal obligations.</p>

    <h2>4. Sharing data</h2>
    <p>We may share data with infrastructure providers, moderation tools, and professional advisers under appropriate safeguards. Profile information you choose to publish may be visible to other platform users.</p>

    <h2>5. Retention</h2>
    <p>We keep personal data only as long as needed for the purposes above, including legal, accounting, and dispute-resolution requirements.</p>

    <h2>6. Your rights</h2>
    <p>Depending on applicable law, you may have rights to access, rectify, erase, restrict, object, or port your data, and to withdraw consent. Contact us to exercise these rights.</p>

    <h2>7. Security</h2>
    <p>We apply technical and organisational measures to protect data, including access controls and encrypted transport (HTTPS). No online service can guarantee absolute security.</p>

    <h2>8. International transfers</h2>
    <p>If data is processed outside the UK, we use appropriate safeguards such as standard contractual clauses where required.</p>

    <h2>9. Contact</h2>
    <p>Privacy enquiries: <a href="/contact">Contact page</a>.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<%- include('../partials/footer') %>
